# Angular OnPush Requirement

All Angular components in the web app must use `ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush`.

## Why

- Required for zoneless change detection compatibility
- Reduces unnecessary change detection cycles
- Aligns with Angular best practices (signals, immutable inputs)

## Rule

Every `@Component` decorator must include:

```ts
import { ChangeDetectionStrategy } from '@angular/core';

@Component({
  changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush,
  // ...
})
```

## Examples

```
// BAD - defaults to Default strategy
@Component({ selector: 'app-foo', template: '...' })

// GOOD - explicit OnPush
@Component({ selector: 'app-foo', changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush, template: '...' })
```
